Rating: 3
I made this dish for a small dinner party and it was a big hit. I too had difficulty finding fresh cherries and substituted the canned kind (rinsed as suggested). Also, instead of using cherry preserve, I just used 2 tbsp of cherry sauce from the can. It worked out great. The cherries were a little soft but no one seemed to mind!

Rating: 4
This is truly delicious! Our cherry season just ended so I substituted rinsed, canned cherries (one can of pitted cherries, halved, equals one cup)and adjusted the sauce cooking time. Next time,I'll make the sauce and use it with duck breast. Easy and impressive!

